What a great question! Add your thoughts and suggestions below, too! There’s plenty of great answers to this question! 

There is so much love and clarity by focusing on your present moment, by learning how to accept yourself fully.

The number one thing I try to teach is total self-acceptance without shame. 

There’s 4 days left until my Art Of Letting Go workshop! If you’re ready to feel energetically lighter, register for the private session at IamLettingGo.net

node.text:
I said it once, and ill repeat it: arguing is the lowest form of communication.

What we want is to be heard, to enter safe forms of communication, and to share how we think and feel. We have to let go of arguing and replace it with listening and collaboration.

Arguing as a vessel does not get you there? Unless you get paid to go on TV and argue, there's no reason to use that tactic in real life. Listen all thriugh on this one for some solid techniques and practices.

There's 9 days left until my Art Of Letting Go workshop starts where you'll learn all about “How To Let Go”. Visit the link in my bio or iamlettinggo.net to get your spot! You dont want to miss this workshop. 

#SylvesterMcNutt

node.text:
What a fun chat on identity. Thank you to everyone who joined me live here on Instagram. 

Here’s the structure of the chat: 

• the question I’m curious about answering
• an explanation of lower and higher vibrations
• an explanation of genuine self-compassion
• step one
• step two
• step three
• summary

node.text:
The first step towards letting go is giving up the obsessive chase to be liked, agreed with, accepted, validated. It's fantastic when we find agreement and when we are validated, that is good for everyone. However, we have to make sure we are not self-abandoning for "approval".

That in itself gives you a great deal of freedom and reign to live your most authentic self.

Comment below and let me know what your thoughts are! 

On August 13th, I'm doing an immersive deep dive into the subject of letting go. I'll teach you how to let go and how to enable the peace of mind you deserve. Go to the link in my bio and reserve your spot in "The Art Of Letting Go Workshop."

node.title: Letting Go: Let Go Of Other People's Approval

node.text:
Speak good energy and life into yourself every single day. Always use self-compasdion when you talk about your journey. As a consequence of self-compassion, your vibration will change. As a consequence of a raised vibration, you'll find it easier to set boundaries.

I'm going live tomorrow on Instagram. Send me your questions or topics you’d like me to cover via direct message. Turn on my post notifications, so you don't miss when I go live!

node.title: How Do I Speak Up For Myself

node.text:
This clip is from a mini-episode of the Free Your Energy podcast. Grab it on Spotify or iTunes.

If you enjoy long-form podcasts, you'll love hearing me jam with world-class teachers, storytellers, and people with immense passion.

During the week, I do mini-episodes on different topics that inspire me!  If you NEED more words on overthinking, I have a mini-course called “How To Stop Overthinking.” You can grab that from Sylvestermcnutt.net/courses

I hope you get into the activity, action, and into the mud! It's the only way to create what you're envisioning!

Focusing on what is outside of you is a path to stress, anxiety, confusion, and who knows what else.

I believe in choosing to see where your opportunities are, to see what you can do with what you have • comment below; let me know what your thoughts are below!

At 5 pm PST, I’ll be jamming on The Art Of Letting Go. If this is a pain point in your life right now, respectfully, I invite you to join me tonight. This will offer energy, the framework, and a safe space to process “letting go.”

If you can’t make it live, but you still need this, an on-demand video will be released for all those who have registered.

I’ll be sending out the link to all those who have registered soon! I can’t wait to jam with you! 

How to register: IamLettingGo.Net (the link is in my bio as well). I'm so excited to talk about this subject!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sylvester McNutt III in Phoenix, Arizona. May be an image of text that says 'When it is time to go, be gone. Stop convincing yourself to stay in unwanted environments. mcnutt'.

node.text:
Drop a 💛 if these words from Care Package: A Path To Deep Healing resonant with you today! 

If it’s an environment that’s marked as “unwanted,” please, with grace, allow yourself to spend time elsewhere.

At first, yes, your ego may take a bruising. You’re allowed to grieve and honor that pain. You are also allowed to key it go. 

And then I hope you come to see that trying to be In “unwanted” spaces is a waste of your time. There’s abundance, love, and joy out here for us. It’s our job to claim it, go there, and create it for ourselves and others.

node.text:
Let go of the need to be right.

Let go of living in your past stories. 

Let go of living in the constant struggle of always trying to plan the future.

Embrace the now, the unknown, what is, and a paradigm shift will occur.

Embrace your ability to adjust, adapt, and evolve.

Many people struggle with letting go. Join me this Friday for a powerful CONVERSATION + Q&A that will help you lean into letting go. How? The link is in my bio or go to IamLettingGo.net

Letting go of the NEED to chase other’s validation will give you emotional freedom.

Yes, validation is good and feels good, and it helps us feel like we belong. Yes, however, we must practice living our most genuine life and being okay with the potential loss of another not liking us.

I hope you practice loving kindness and offer yourself compassion.

I'm so excited to do my next workshop on letting go (this Friday). If you'd like to learn HOW TO LET GO, join me at IamLettingGo.net

node.text:
Life Update: I’m doing well. I’m grateful, privileged, and thankful for where life is. For the last two years, I was deep into a “yes phase.”

The consequence of that phase has been new connections here in Arizona and new business opportunities worldwide. And a state of freedom.

I said yes to new people, new ideas, and new opportunities and pushed myself beyond my comfort zones.

Now, I’m in a “deepening phase.” I find myself interested in clarity, minimization, and joy.

Brenè Brown, in her book Dare To Lead, says joy is the most vulnerable emotion. I feel grateful and privileged that I get to experience that often.

This is my LAST WEEK working on my ninth book. After working on it for two years, I trust the words, I love the energy, and it’s time for me to close the chapter of writing it. I feel ready to “let go” of this project and ideas. Being an author full-time is a profound honor, one that I never take for granted, and I'm glad I didn't give in to the pressure of production. 

Oh, and on the sobriety thing, I’ve reached 132 sober from alcohol. That’s the longest I’ve gone since I started drinking at the age of 21. Still not sure what my long-term play is, but I’m aligned with the moment and the moment has me feeling like my energy is free.

I hope you have the most beautiful week! I put some of my favorite words on the back of this carousel. I hope those serve you as they have served me sincerely. #SylvesterMcNutt
